  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u201c \u0b95\u0bcb\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe \u0b95\u0bcb \u0b95\u0bae\u201d \u0baa\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b85\u0b95\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bc8 : \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0baa\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0ba9\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0bb5\u0bb4\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd\u00a0-\u00a0\u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\"Kota Ko Kama\" protest site not removed by soldiers: Peaceful protest will be allowed - President Ranil",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "It has been mentioned in the meeting with foreign diplomats led by the President that the news circulating on social media regarding the Kota Ko Kama protest is false and the protest site has not been cleared by the security forces.",
        "President Ranil Wickremesinghe has assured foreign diplomats that Sri Lanka will be committed to ensuring the right to peaceful and non-violent assembly.",
        "During the meeting with foreign diplomats on the 22nd, the President stated his position as above.",
        "The meeting was held to clarify to the foreign diplomats about the expulsion of those gathered at the Presidential Secretariat.",
        "President Ranil Wickremesinghe said that the government will confirm both Article 21 of the International Covenant on Civil and Political Rights and Article 14(1)(b) of the Constitution, which refers to peaceful assembly.",
        "The President made it clear that the advice given by the American Civil Liberties Union should not allow protesters to disrupt government buildings and disrupt government property for other purposes.",
        "The diplomats were briefed on the steps taken to ensure permission to protest peacefully within the city without harming property or life.",
        "Vikaramadevi Park, New City Hall, Hyde Park and Kempel Ground will be allowed for peaceful protest with all facilities.",
        "It was mentioned during the meeting that the news circulating on social media about the Kota Ko Kama protest was false and the security forces had not removed the protest sites."
      ],
